Functions for calculations

Define a function to calculate standard error

se <- function(x) {
  sd(x) / sqrt(length(x))
}

Function to calculate heating rates and slope

the following function computes the overall change in temperature (delta) and the maximum rate of change of temperature (slope) based on the provided temperature measures and a specified time interval.

ht <- function(heating, time_interval = 10) {
  delta <- heating[length(heating)] - heating[1]
  tmp_slope <- c()
  count = 1
  while (count < length(heating)) {
    tmp <- (heating[count + 2] - heating[count]) / time_interval
    tmp_slope <- c(tmp_slope, tmp)
    count = count + 1
  }
  slope <- max(na.omit(tmp_slope))
  return(c(delta, slope))
}

Summary calculations per side

Ventral side

Using the ventral side measures of both black and black-and-white colour morphs calculate the overall change in temperature (delta) and the maximum rate of change of temperature (slope)

# Create an empty tibble to store data
datos <- tibble(
  code = character(),
  morph = character(),
  side = character(),
  delta_temp = double(),
  slope = character(),
  weight = double(),
  width = double()
)


for (arch in list.files(pattern = "*_v.TXT")) {
  df <- read_delim(arch, col_names = FALSE, delim = "\t")
  tmp <- df[, 4]
  colnames(tmp) <- c("temp_egg")
  code <- arch %>% str_replace("_v.TXT", "")
  measures <- ht(heating = tmp$temp_egg, time_interval = 20)
  morph <- ref$morph[grepl(paste0("\\b", code, "\\b"), ref$code)]
  weight <- ref$weight[grepl(paste0("\\b", code, "\\b"), ref$code)]
  width <- ref$width[grepl(paste0("\\b", code, "\\b"), ref$code)]
  tmp <- tibble(
    code = code,
    side = "ventral",
    delta_temp = measures[1],
    slope = measures[2],
    morph = morph,
    weight = weight,
    width = width
  )
  datos <- rbind(datos, tmp)
}

ventral<-datos
